description: From Latin trifurcus, from tri- (“three”) + furca (“fork”).

entries.meaning: Forked, with three tines or points.

verbs.description: trifurcate (third-person singular simple present trifurcates, present participle trifurcating, simple past and past participle trifurcated)

entries.meaning: To divide or fork into three channels or branches.
